Big shoutout to @aldryn for having us on as a guest for this great video giving you 12 drone tips from different industry operators.
.
Our tip for beginners and those new to the drone industry is to start flying from day one holding the remote control with the pinching method.
It’s always a controversial one as so many fly with their thumbs.
@mrsteelefpv uses the pinch method and most professional drone pilots we know do as well. More precise control for cinematic shots and safer in our opinion.
.
Which way do hold the sticks?
.
Be sure to SUBSCRIBE to @aldryn YouTube channel if you haven’t already. We’ll put a link to the video and his channel in our instagram stories.

EVENT ANNOUNCEMENT:
Come see DRONEGEAR Executive Producer Matt Feige @ffinmatt will be speaking at the  2019 Hollywood Drone Expo TODAY!
.
sUAS News, in association with the Society Of Aerial Cinematography @the_soac and ICG Local 600, is proud to present the 2019 Hollywood Drone Symposium.
.
What:  Gathering of Film and TV industry professional drone operators and their supporters. The program will center on lessons learned by the community since the inception of 14 CFR Part 107, what aspects are working, as well as possible changes that would make for the wider adoption and safe use of drone technology.
.
Where: Filmtools, 1400 West Burbank Blvd. Burbank, CA 91506
.
When: December 7th, 2019 at 10:00 am to 4:00 pm •

We’ve had multiple production companies lose these SSD’s and readers over they years and it’s thousands of dollars to replace.
This case helps transport it safely and reduces the risk of data loss and actual physical loss by production and damage when being shipped.
Thank you to Pelican for making this custom@piece of gear I’ve wanted ever since the inspire 2 came out.

@jmoustache filming @stanevansphoto with the new @tiffencompany STEADIMATE-S which is designed for your @djiglobal Ronin-S/SC.
This system helps users get more consistent and stable shots for long term use with no up and down movement from when your arms get tired.
A couple of major benefits is the support the vest gives your entire back. Another being you can let the arm take the weight of the entire camera and gimbal whilst you make any adjustments to camera settings when you need to, which means you don’t have to set it down for a rest and you can keep shooting and move onto the next shot!
.
We’ve been using the STEADIMATE-S for several weeks now and absolutely love it!
.
If you’re in LA be sure to RSVP for the Steadimate-S launch party Tiffen Technical Center in Burbank, DJI will also be there this Tuesday October 15th.

🇵🇪
@drone.pilot here with an aerial shot from Peru.
This top down shot shows the incredible graduated terrace farming that was developed by the Wari culture and other peoples of the south-central Andes before 1000 AD, centuries before they were used by the Inca, who adopted them.
When flying the drone I noticed this everywhere in the distance. Truly incredible how they adopted such a harsh climate and have made farming work for them.
This shot was taken as the sun was setting creating beautiful shadows over the vast rolling hills and mountains.
Taken with DJI Mavic 2 & @tiffencompany ND4/PL
•

MANTA RAYS 🖤

Text and drone footage by me, @camilladellion : ⠀
I had my first encounter with manta rays when I lived in Hawaii in 2015. We were kayaking in Kealakekua Bay and 2 huge rays curiously swam up next to us. Ever since then I’ve been in love.
⠀
There are few things in the world as magnificent as the manta ray. They’re dancing their way through the ocean in such a majestic way. Throughout the years I’ve had numerous encounters with them, and the experience never gets smaller or less fascinating. Despite the happiness I experience with every encounter, the sadness of knowing just how threatened and vulnerable these creatures are, is always very present.
⠀
The mantas suffer the consequences of human activities - I’ve seen it with my own eyes, the manta rays are swimming around in seas of plastic. The biggest threaths  to the manta is climate change, habitat loss, overfishing, bycatch and entanglement in fishing nets.
⠀
But there is another awful treath to them - they’re targeted for their gill plates which are used in traditional Chinese medicin believed to cure cancer. The demand for the gill plates is huge and mantas are slaughtered every day.
⠀
The manta rays become sexually mature at the age of 5 and in 2-5 years they give birth to one or two pups. Their reproduction is way to slow to keep up with the slaughtering.
⠀
So what can we do, you and me? Donate money to organizations that protect manta rays, spread awareness and strive to live more sustainable. Support and get involved in the eco-tourism around manta rays, this can be an economic replacement to the fishing. While the gill plate trade is estimated to generate around 5 million dollars annually, manta ray tourism is estimated to generate 140 million dollar annually. Manta Rays are definitely worth more alive than dead.
⠀
Swipe right to see footage from a market in Guangzhou, China taken by @captain_smulders who always awake me with her footage.
⠀

💯
We’re excited to announce that DRONEGEAR will be exclusively using the @indemnis_ NEXUS parachute system on our DJI Inspire 2’s for safe UAS operations over people.
We will be reviewing the system in depth and doing a live test on the system and will publish to YouTube and our blog.
We only partner with best companies in the industry and after many hours of our team researching other companies we came to the conclusion that @indemnis_ is the industry leader.
We’re excited to test the system in real life and apply to our working fleet of drones on the jobs where necessary to keep our 100% zero incident safety rating.
We encourage drone companies around the world to look into applying this parachute safety mechanism. You never know what can happen and having a system like this gives you and the client peace of mind.
.
📸 @indemnis_
